              <tr><td colspan="3">    <table width="600" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
    <tr><td width="200" valign="top"><b>Langseax</b><br>
MAGIC ITEM <br>
Skill: 1HS&nbsp;&nbsp;Atk Delay: 23<br>
DMG: 6<br>
WT: 4.0<br>
Class: WAR<br>
Race: ALL</td>
    
    <td width="100" align="center" valign="top">
    <b>Item Icon</b><br>
    None Available</td>

    <td width="150" valign="top">
    <b>Obtained From</b><br>
    Quest<br>
Level 20</td>
    <td width="150" valign="top">
    <b>Additional Info</b><br>
    Type: Weapon, 1HS<br>
Damage Per Second: 5.65<br>
Zone(s): halas<br>
Last Updated: 04/11/00<br>
</td></tr>
    </table>
    <br><br>
    <b>Description</b><br>
Talk to Renth McLanis in the tavern across from Mac's Kilts in Halas.  He will tell you of a crime that has taken place and will ask you if you can hunt the murderer.  If you say yes, he will ask you to go and see Dok in Dok's Cigars.  Dok will tell you more about the crime, and then suggest that you talk to the leader of Clan McMannus.  Head to the fishing village located in West Karanas and speak to the leader, and you will learn that Frostbite can track people if he has a piece of clothing.  Head back to Halas and talk with Dok again.  He will tell you that he sold a sweaty shirt to Tundra Jack.  Now off to find Tundra Jack, who roams the plains of Everfrost and is constantly hunted by high level characters.  Talk to him, and he will tell you that Iceberg is using it for a collar and that you can have it if you distract Iceberg with his favorite meal, the Lion Delight.  
<br><br>
Back to Halas again and speak to Teria O'Danos.  She will give you a quest on how to obtain the Lion's Delight.  Take the Lion Delight to Iceberg and receive the sweaty shirt.  Now run to the village and give the shirt to Frostbite.  Frostbite will lead you right to the murderer, who will either be Paglan or Basil.  Kill whomever Frostbite leads you to, and hope that a Barbarian's head is dropped.  Return this head to Renth and you will receive the Langseax if you have Basil's head or the Langseax of the Wolves if it is Paglan's head.  
<br><br>
Note: You need a very good faction to complete this quest.<br><br>
